= News (2008-09-30)
== Ruby-GNOME2 0.18.0 released
((*Posted by kou on 2008-09-30 (Tue) 16:02:06*))

Ruby-GNOME2 0.18.0 is out. Enjoy!

This release fixes some memory leak bugs and has new
experimental packages.

== Highlights

* Fix memory leak bugs.
* Add experimental packages:
  * Ruby/GtkSourceView2
  * Ruby/GooCanvas

== Downloads

((<URL:http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=53614>))

:ruby-gtk2-x.x.x.tar.gz
  The minimum package which includes Ruby/GLib2, Ruby/ATK, Ruby/GdkPixbuf2, Ruby/Pango, Ruby/GTK2.

:ruby-gnome2-all-x.x.x.tar.gz
  All of Ruby-GNOME2 libraries.

== Changes

Ruby/GLib:
  * mkmf-gnome2.rb: add check_cairo. [Kouhei Sutou]
  * fixed memory leaks. [Kouhei Sutou]
    * [#2110165] Gdk::Pixbuf memory leak
  * install glib-enum-types.h. [Andy Spencer]
    * [#2106938] Install glib-enum-types.h

Ruby/GTK2:
  * add GTK+ 2.12 related bindings. [Guillaume Cottenceau]
  * fixed initialize order. [Kouhei Sutou]
    * [#2113491] Incorrect initialize order (compiling with mingw)

Ruby/GooCanvas [NEW][EXPERIMENTAL]:
  * added. [Kouhei Sutou]

Ruby/Pango:
  * fixed memory leaks. [Kouhei Sutou]

Ruby/GtkSourceView2 [NEW][EXPERIMENTAL]:
  * add. [yselkowitz]

